  "Title": "MikroTik: WiFi Configuration – Simple Setup",
  "Link": "https://www.shellhacks.com/mikrotik-wifi-configuration-simple-setup/",
  "Content": "\u003cdiv class=\"entry-content\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"aa-8d29358d3be5317fa9a16d7403a7da72 aa-before-content\" id=\"aa-8d29358d3be5317fa9a16d7403a7da72\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe very common usage of a MikroTik WiFi router is to create a password protected wireless access point (WAP).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn this post I will show a very quick overview for beginners on setting up the WAP on the MikroTik router with the WiFi.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo start configuring the WiFi on the MikroTik router is is required to connect to it using a WinBox/WinFig (RouterOS graphical configuration tools) or over SSH, for once who prefer working in a command line.\u003cspan id=\"more-4923\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"note-lnk\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCool Tip:\u003c/strong\u003e List MikroTik RouterOS firewall rules! \u003ca href=\"/mikrotik-list-firewall-rules/\"\u003eRead more →\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eMikroTik WiFi Configuration\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe important part is to make sure that the WAP is protected, so the first step is to create a security profile.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo create the security profile in the WinBox/WinFig interface, go to the “\u003cem\u003eWireless\u003c/em\u003e“, open the “\u003cem\u003eSecurity Profiles\u003c/em\u003e” tab and click on the “➕” or “\u003cem\u003eAdd New\u003c/em\u003e“:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/xmikrotik_create_wireless_security_profile.png.pagespeed.ic.aRKEeQ8o2o.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"964\" height=\"638\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4937\" srcset=\"https://www.shellhacks.com/wp-content/uploads/xmikrotik_create_wireless_security_profile.png.pagespeed.ic.aRKEeQ8o2o.png 964w, https://www.shellhacks.com/wp-content/uploads/xmikrotik_create_wireless_security_profile-700x463.png.pagespeed.ic.6thvv-Dvcq.png 700w, https://www.shellhacks.com/wp-content/uploads/xmikrotik_create_wireless_security_profile-768x508.png.pagespeed.ic.X-adb1OTAV.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 964px) 100vw, 964px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThink of a profile name, e.g. \u003cem\u003eprofile-0\u003c/em\u003e, choose the “dynamic keys” mode, select the “WPA2 PSK” as the authentication type, set the WiFi password in the “WPA2 Pre-Shared Key” field and click on “OK”.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the command line interface all these can be done as follows:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u0026gt; /interface wireless security-profiles \\\n             add name=\u003cem\u003eprofile-0\u003c/em\u003e authentication-types=wpa2-psk mode=dynamic-keys \\\n             wpa2-pre-shared-key=\u003cem\u003epassw0rd\u003c/em\u003e\n\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe WiFi interface may be disabled at first time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo enable it go to the “\u003cem\u003eWireless\u003c/em\u003e“, open the “\u003cem\u003eWiFi Interfaces\u003c/em\u003e” (by default: \u003ccode\u003ewlan1\u003c/code\u003e), right-click on it and then click on “Enable”:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/xmikrotik_enable_wireless_interface.png.pagespeed.ic.5emKX5rUds.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"963\" height=\"637\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4938\" srcset=\"https://www.shellhacks.com/wp-content/uploads/xmikrotik_enable_wireless_interface.png.pagespeed.ic.5emKX5rUds.png 963w, https://www.shellhacks.com/wp-content/uploads/xmikrotik_enable_wireless_interface-700x463.png.pagespeed.ic.TwGEXC6ebS.png 700w, https://www.shellhacks.com/wp-content/uploads/xmikrotik_enable_wireless_interface-768x508.png.pagespeed.ic.3QiCXmDd-N.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 963px) 100vw, 963px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThen double-click on the \u003ccode\u003ewlan1\u003c/code\u003e WiFi interface, select the previously created security profile and click on “OK”:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/xmikrotik_wireless_select_security_profile.png.pagespeed.ic.EP1_EY0IT6.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"532\" height=\"557\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4939\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo enable the \u003ccode\u003ewlan1\u003c/code\u003e WiFi interface and select the security profile from the command line:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u0026gt; /interface wireless enable wlan1\n\u0026gt; /interface wireless set wlan1 security-profile=\u003cem\u003eprofile-0\u003c/em\u003e\n\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAfter this simple WiFi configuration you should able to find the SSID of the MikroTik WAP and connect to it using the password that has been set in the “WPA2 Pre-Shared Key” field during the security profile creation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"heateorSssClear\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"heateor_sss_sharing_container heateor_sss_horizontal_sharing\" data-heateor-sss-href=\"https://www.shellhacks.com/mikrotik-wifi-configuration-simple-setup/\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"heateor_sss_sharing_title\" style=\"font-weight:bold\"\u003eWas it useful? Share this post with the world!\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"heateor_sss_sharing_ul\"\u003e\u003ca aria-label=\"Facebook\" class=\"heateor_sss_facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shellhacks.com%2Fmikrotik-wifi-configuration-simple-setup%2F\" title=\"Facebook\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size:32px!important;box-shadow:none;display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"heateor_sss_svg\" style=\"background-color:#3c589a;width:87.5px;height:31.25px;display:inline-block;opacity:1;float:left;font-size:32px;box-shadow:none;display:inline-block;font-size:16px;padding:0 4px;vertical-align:middle;background-repeat:repeat;overflow:hidden;padding:0;cursor:pointer;box-sizing:content-box\"\u003e\u003csvg style=\"display:block;\" focusable=\"false\" aria-hidden=\"true\" xmlns=\"http://www